Around the globe, headlines break the news: a scandal takes down an Indian cotton tycoon; a Chinese opium trader dies of an apparent overdose; bombings in Strasbourg and Vienna; the death of an American steel magnate... No one sees the connective thread between these seemingly random events‚Äîno one, that is, except the great Sherlock Holmes, who has discerned a deliberate web of death and destruction. At its center sits a singularly sinister spider: Moriarty.


Holmes‚Äô investigation into Moriarty‚Äôs plot becomes more dangerous as it leads him and Watson out of London to France, Germany and finally Switzerland. title: Mame
description:
Lucille Ball stars in this film of the blockbuster Broadway musical that tells the story of the flamboyant, unconventional and, above all, glamorous Mame.

In 1928, nine-year-old Patrick Dennis (Kirby Furlong) comes to live with his Auntie Mame (Ball), who has a generous heart, believes life should be a party and collects fascinating friends. But the stock market crash of 1929 ends a decade-long fete and forces Mame into disastrous forays as an actress and a working woman, before doing what she knows best: marrying well. Once again wealthy, Mame returns to her self-appointed task of liberating friends and family from their bourgeois sensibility.

Based on the novel, Broadway play and Broadway musical.

title: LIVE | Great News From Supreme Court About Elections | Big Order Of Chief Justice | Dunya News
description:
#supremecourtofpakistan #imrankhan #shahbazsharif #cheifjusticeofpakistan #umaratabandial 

LIVE | Great News From Supreme Court About Elections | Big Order Of Chief Justice | Dunya News

The five-member Supreme Court bench will resume on Tuesday hearing of PTI's petition against postponement of Punjab and Khyber Pakhtunkhwa elections.

The bench headed by Chief Justice Umar Atta Bandial will start proceedings at 11:30 am. Justice Ijazul Ahsan, Justice Muneeb Akhtar, Justice Aminuddin Khan and Justice Jamal Mandukhel are the members of the bench.

During Monday‚Äôs proceedings, the Supreme Court issued notices to the Federation, Election Commission of Pakistan (ECP) and Attorney General. Notices were also issued to the petitioners including the caretaker governments and governors of Punjab and Khyber Pakhtunkhwa.

The petition, moved by Senator Barrister Syed Ali Zafar, sought from the apex court to set aside the March 22 notification of the ECP for being ‚Äòunconstitutional‚Äô and ‚Äòillegal‚Äô. Barrister Zafar described the ECP notification as the ‚Äú9/11 of Pakistan‚Äôs Consti¬¨tution‚Äù and asked the SC to order the ECP to hold elections on April 30 as announced by President Dr Arif Alvi in pursuance of the Supreme Court directive issued on March 1.

Chief Justice (CJP) Bandial on Monday observed that the spirit of the Constitution does not envisage the making or breaking of governments, rather focuses on ensuring good governance and bringing happiness to the people by protecting their rights.

At the same time, the CJP also shared his worries regarding the prevailing hostility, animosity, and bitterness which he said had been ‚Äúsown into our polity‚Äù, while questioning the role political leaders were playing to restore peace and calm in society and seeking a ‚Äòcommitment‚Äô from parties in this regard.

title: Lonely Gimmick - Beaches (Official Video)
description:
Spotify - https://open.spotify.com/artist/0Kr7NcQJfzHQp4CVBbhlzO?promo=
Apple Music - https://music.apple.com/us/artist/lonely-gimmick/1518328809
Amazon Music - https://music.amazon.co.uk/artists/B08BX83TLF/lonely-gimmick
Patreon - https://www.patreon.com/lonelygimmick
Download/Bandcamp Link - https://lonelygimmick.bandcamp.com
Instagram - https://www.instagram.com/lonelygimmick
Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/lonelygimmick
SoundCloud - https://soundcloud.com/lonelygimmick
Twitter - https://twitter.com/LonelyGimmick

"Beaches" is the brand new single from the anonymous artist known as "Lonely Gimmick". Set to be released on March 31st 2023, it is their fourth official single to date.

Crafted over a five year span, the track features drums and percussion performed by renowned producer/drummer "Richie Stevens" (Tina Turner, Boy George/Culture Club, Smudge All Stars, SpaceMonkeyz, George Clinton, Lee Scratch Perry). Good friend "Marcus Engwall" lends his lush, sad boy choral tones for a touch of backing vocals. Mixed by Lonely Gimmick themselves and mastered by the accomplished Olly Betts (The Duke Spirit, "Grumpy Days" engineer) at "Crow's nest studios", ‚ÄúBeaches‚Äù is a slice of Lo-fi pop sizzle sure to draw you in with its afro pop inspired guitar riffs and unpretentious charm.

Gently opening with a fuzzy Glockenspiel-inspired synth and nothing more, anticipation starts to build as stray drowned out guitar chords ring out across the sonic landscape. Just when the intro has lulled it‚Äôs listener into a sense of tranquility, soft yet firm vocals kick in at a brisk pace:  

"I can see beaches, scrolling with my thumbs, through miles of smiles and pictures of suns, there's really not much, not much to repeat, with all these modern day techniques". 

In a similar vein to the quote: "Don't let the internet rush you, nobody is posting their failures," LG‚Äôs lyrics are a comment on the apparent happiness in other people's lives when viewed through social media. The artist reflects on how things can easily seem hopeless when everyone else appears to be achieving more than you. Everything has been done before so why even bother? That said, there is a flip side to social media and it‚Äôs impact, which LG explores in the first verse: "I can see beaches on my phone, scrolling with my thumbs now I don't feel alone". Whilst comparing ourselves to others may sometimes make us feel inadequate, social media can help fend off loneliness and provide a connection to humanity and the wider world. The message being that it‚Äôs a significant catch 22 of our times; damned if you use it, damned if you don't.  

Throughout "Beaches" Lonely Gimmick takes the listener with them to "the grass is always greener" contemplations while you wait on a London train ("Carshalton Beeches, I have never been, but I always see it on my destination screen"). Then to pubs and down back alleys where one‚Äôs soul will become "trapped in concrete". You'll end up being so intoxicated that you'll trip over your own feet. Women will offer to buy you drinks because they like your hair but hate your dirty shoes. You'll read free newspapers such as "The Metro" and "The Evening Standard" that deliver nothing but bad news. All these papers ever seem to tell you is "the end is nigh". But however, despite all this utter bedlam your main worry will be a whiskey drunk neat.

It is interesting to note the song has no real chorus to speak of with no lyrics repeating. The closest moments to a chorus are funky afro-pop guitar fueled breaks with accompanying tambourine. "Beaches" hints at an "LCD Soundsystem" song structure mixed with "Vampire Weekend" or even "The War on Drugs‚Äù. It is one long continuous loop that builds onto itself, never allowing the possibility of boredom.

Musically ‚ÄúBeaches‚Äù is deceptive, sweeping the audience up with it‚Äôs joyful beat and playful guitar. Beneath the infectious melody, however, lie emotionally stirring lyrics influenced by moments of existential dread. LG has skilfully combined these qualities to create a refreshing, replayable lo-fi pop song with an unexpected depth at it‚Äôs heart.

title: Sherlock Holmes
description:
From director Guy Ritchie (Rocknrolla, Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels) comes an all-new take on the classic master detective Sherlock Holmes starring Robert Downey Jr., Jude Law and Rachel McAdams.

Renowned "consulting detective" Sherlock Holmes (Downey Jr.--Iron Man) has a reputation for solving the most complex mysteries. With the aid of his trusted ally Dr. John Watson (Law--The Aviator), Holmes is unequaled in his pursuit of criminals, relying on his singular powers of observation, his remarkable deductive skills -- and the blunt force of his fists. But now a threat unlike anything Holmes has ever confronted threatens London ... and it's just the challenge he's looking for.

After a string of brutal, ritualistic murders, Holmes and Watson arrive just in time to save the latest victim and uncover the killer, the unrepentant Lord Blackwood (Mark Strong--Body of Lies). Before his hanging, Blackwood warns Holmes that death has no power over him, and when Blackwood's apparent resurrection and latest deadly plot panic London and confound Scotland Yard, Holmes and Watson plunge into a world of the dark arts and startling new technologies, where logic is sometimes the best crime-fighting weapon ... but where a good right hook will often do the job.

And the game is afoot!

title: New BMW M2 review with 0-60mph & auto vs manual!
description:
This is the all-new BMW M2! 

Mat‚Äôs headed over to America to get his hands on this all-new sports coupe, and he‚Äôs about to find out if it‚Äôs a worthy successor to the previous M2, and whether it can compete with the likes of the Porsche Cayman or even the M3! 

Well when it comes to the design, it‚Äôs had a serious overhaul over the regular 2 Series. It‚Äôs got a large squared kidney grille up front, bulging wheel arches over the side, a carbon fibre roof and quad tailpipes at the back. All-in-all, it‚Äôs certainly meaner and more aggressive than the regular 2 Series. 

It‚Äôs a similar story on the inside, with several changes made over the standard car. As you‚Äôd expect there‚Äôs a smattering of M tricolour to be found throughout, a fair bit of carbon fibre, and M-specific digital dial graphics. It also comes with sport bucket seats. 

Then let‚Äôs take a look under the bonnet! It comes with the same 3-litre twin-turbo straight-six as found in the M3, but the output has been dialled down slightly, so it‚Äôll produce 460hp and 550Nm of torque. This power is delivered to the rear wheels only, and unlike the M3, you can pick the M2 up as either a manual or an automatic! 

The price starts from around ¬£65,000, but is it really worth it? There‚Äôs only one way to find out - stick with Mat for this all-new review!

title: Waking Up Free: India‚Äôs Journey Produced By Silambam
description:
This exquisite dance tells the stories of India‚Äôs struggle for independence, and celebrates her heroes, through the dynamic kaleidoscope of dance, in this, the 75th year of Indian Independence. Based on the traditional Maargam format of Bharatanatyam, this original production will weave together the emotive range of classical Indian music and the expressivity of Indian classical dance to take the audience on India‚Äôs journey to freedom and beyond.

From the oppression of the British Raj, to the remarkable stories of the non-violent resistance, led by the heroes of India‚Äôs freedom struggle, and carried through with patriotic fervor by the people of the country. From the grief and heartbreak of Partition, to the hope and optimism of present-day India. Waking Up Free is an original Silambam Houston production that celebrates India‚Äôs journey to Independence through the centuries-old Indian classical dance form Bharatanatyam.

Silambam Houston was founded in 2002 by Dr. Lavanya Rajagopalan, for the promotion and development of the arts, to impart artistic education, and promote young talent in the performing arts.  Their vision is to increase the appreciation and understanding of Indian artistic traditions across cultural boundaries, through comprehensive arts education, outreach, and exceptional arts programming, and by creating opportunities for young artistes to develop, perform, and collaborate.

All performances at Miller Outdoor Theatre are FREE!

Nikah is a powerful and inspiring story of a young girl‚Äôs fight for her social and religious rights. 
Opinionated and confident by nature, Anusha is a beautiful young girl who knows how to stand up for her rights. After losing her mother at a young age, Anusha has been brought up by her aunt, Umaima with a lot of love and care. Umamia is a bit hesitant about Anusha‚Äôs assertiveness and often makes her understand. 
Class fellows and best friends, Anusha and Haris are in love with each other and soon plan to marry. On the contrary, Hamdaan is a handsome young man who belongs to a wealthy family and is the only son of his father. He falls in love with Anusha on his very first meeting with her however is respectful of Anusha‚Äôs choices.
Anusha‚Äôs hope and dreams come crashing down when Haris challenges her thoughts. The supposedly liberal fabric of Haris and his family is exposed when Anusha takes a stand for her rights. Eamon and I have been lucky enough to travel to Mexico in our van since 2018 and we've always been so sad to see the struggling stray dogs and puppies on the streets. We even fostered a sick puppy from Baja in 2019 and drove him back up to Canada where he's happily lived in his furever home for the last 4 years. So, when we met Alex and he said it was his dream to start a dog rescue here in Baja we knew we needed to help! üê∂ üêï üê©

Get caught up on this adventure:
